== Basmati Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Tandoori Chicken ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Thigh{260%g} to the pan and season with @salt and @pepper.

Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

== Masala Curry ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the chicken has browned, add the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, garlic and @Tandoori Masala Mix{1%sachet} to the pan. Mix well and cook for ~{1%minute}, until fragrant.

Next, stir in the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water for the Curry{125%ml}.

> See pantry for amount of water for the curry.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat so the sauce simmers gently.

Cook until the chicken is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Finishing ==

Once the chicken is cooked, stir in the @Creme Fraiche{75%g}, @Mango Chutney{40%g} and @Butter{20%g} until the butter is melted.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @?salt and @?pepper if needed.

Remove from the heat. Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

== To Serve ==

Share the rice out between your serving bowls.

Spoon over the tandoori chicken masala curry.

Sprinkle over the @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} to finish.

Enjoy!